\ globals: `variable` declares (value 0), `to` assigns and auto-creates at the
\ REPL; `variables` ( -- arr ) answers one { :name :value :type } frame per
\ global, oldest first, live values; `vars` pretty-prints them.

variables . cr                          \ [ ] (no globals at startup)

variable x
x .
42 to x
x .
99 to x
x .
variable y
"hello" to y
y .
< 1 2 3 > to y
y .
cr

\ === variables: one frame per global, oldest first, live values ===
variables .
variables [: :name @ :] map . cr        \ [ :x :y ]

\ constants, symbols, and colon words are not globals
symbol marker
variables size . cr                     \ 2 still (PI, E, TAU never appear)

\ composes with the dataset machinery
[ 1 2 3 ] to z
:blue to hue
variables frames>dataset 3 headn

\ === vars pretty-prints each frame ===
vars
